{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes the EF-hand calcium-binding domain-containing proteins SPT21 (spermatogenesis-associated protein 21). SPT21 is involved in the differentiation of haploid spermatids [[cite:PUB00094149]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>Many calcium-binding proteins belong to the same evolutionary family and share a type of calcium-binding domain known as the EF-hand. This type of domain consists of a twelve residue loop flanked on both sides by a twelve residue Î±-helical domain. In an EF-hand loop the calcium ion is coordinated in a pentagonal bipyramidal configuration. The six residues involved in the binding are in positions 1, 3, 5, 7, 9 and 12; these residues are denoted by X, Y, Z, -Y, -X and -Z. The invariant Glu or Asp at position 12 provides two oxygens for liganding Ca (bidentate ligand). Ca2 binding induces a conformational change in the EF-hand motif, leading to the activation or inactivation of target proteins. EF-hands tend to occur in pairs or higher copy numbers [[cite:PUB00023349], [cite:PUB00081528], [cite:PUB00004973], [cite:PUB00081532], [cite:PUB00081536]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR47500" "EF-HAND CALCIUM-BINDING DOMAIN-CONTAINING PROTEIN"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Spermatogenesis-associated protein 21", "short" "SPT21"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 222, "taxa" 991, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 560, "sets" 0, "proteins" 560, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 342}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR043520", :literature {"PUB00004973" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Kawasaki H" "Kretsinger RH."], "ISO_journal" nil, "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "Protein P